3.1 Pagination Example
Paginates through the Opt Out Affidavits data:






Find the Number of Rows



Use the stats endpoints i.e.,

data.cms.gov/data-api/v1/dataset/{ID}/data-viewer/stats
data.cms.gov/data-api/v1/dataset/{ID}/data/stats




3.1.1 THIS WORKS:
“https://data.cms.gov/data-api/v1/dataset/9887a515-7552-4693-bf58-735c77af46d7/data/stats?filter[ex][path]=State%20Code&filter[ex][value]=GA”
“https://data.cms.gov/data-api/v1/dataset/9887a515-7552-4693-bf58-735c77af46d7/data?size=5&filter[ex][path]=State%20Code&filter[ex][value]=GA”

# accessURL |&gt; 
#   req_perform_iterative(
#     next_req = iterate_with_offset(start = 1, offset = 5000)) |&gt; 
#   resp_body_json()

offset_sequence &lt;- \(found, limit = 5000) {

  if (found &lt;= limit) 
    return(found)

  seq.int(
    from = 0, 
    to = if ((found %% 5) == 0) found else (limit + found), 
    by = limit)
}

